-- National Petroleum Construction Plans $400 Million Marine Fleet Expansion
-- Ayesha Daya
-- 2010-06-20T06:25:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/national-petroleum-construction-plans-400-million-marine-fleet-expansion.html

          
          
             National Petroleum Construction Co.,
an Abu Dhabi government-controlled oil-services company, plans
to invest $400 million in expanding its marine fleet.  
 Earlier this month it placed an order with Shanghai Zhenhua
Heavy Industry Co. for a heavy-lift pipelay vessel, scheduled
for delivery by the third quarter 2012, it said in a statement
received by e-mail today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
